#
# This file is interpreted as shell script.
# Put your custom mwan4 action here, they will
# be executed with each netifd hotplug interface event
# on interfaces for which mwan4 is enabled.
#
# There are three main environment variables that are passed to this script.
#
# $ACTION
#      <ifup>         Is called by netifd and mwan4track.
#      <ifdown>       Is called by netifd and mwan4track.
#      <connected>    Is only called by mwan4track if tracking was successful.
#      <disconnected> Is only called by mwan4track if tracking has failed.
# $INTERFACE	Name of the interface an action relates to (e.g. "wan" or "wwan").
# $DEVICE	Physical device name of the interface the action relates to (e.g. "eth0" or "wwan0").
#               Note: On an ifdown event, $DEVICE is not available, use $INTERFACE instead.
#
# Further documentation can be found here:
# https://docs.openwrt.melmac.ca/mwan4/
